<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> Kalachakranet (2006). <i>Tantric Practice</i>. Source: <a href="http://buddhism.kalachakranet.org/tantra_practice.html" class="external autonumber" title="http://buddhism.kalachakranet.org/tantra_practice.html" rel="nofollow">[5]</a> (Source: January 3, 2008)</li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Patrul_Rinpoche" title="Patrul Rinpoche">Rinpoche, Patrul</a> (author); Brown, Kerry (ed.); and Sharma, Sima (ed.)(1994). <i>The Words of My Perfect Teacher</i> (Tibetan title: <i>kunzang lama'i shelung</i>). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. With a forward by the Dalai Lama. San Francisco, California, USA: HarperCollins<i>Publishers</i>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0060664495" class="internal">ISBN 0-06-066449-5</a> (cloth: alk. paper). P.416</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Patrul_Rinpoche" title="Patrul Rinpoche">Rinpoche, Patrul</a> (author); Brown, Kerry (ed.); and Sharma, Sima (ed.)(1994). <i>The Words of My Perfect Teacher</i> (Tibetan title: <i>kunzang lama'i shelung</i>). Translated by the Padmakara Translation Group. With a forward by the Dalai Lama. San Francisco, California, USA: HarperCollins<i>Publishers</i>. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0060664495" class="internal">ISBN 0-06-066449-5</a> (cloth: alk. paper). P.442</li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> Bucknell, Roderick &amp; Stuart-Fox, Martin (1986). <i>The Twilight Language: Explorations in Buddhist Meditation and Symbolism</i>. Curzon Press: London. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0312825404" class="internal">ISBN 0-312-82540-4</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> On the 'five Ms', see Benjamin Walker, <i>The Hindu World</i>, vol. I (New York: Praeger, 1968), p.221; on the five 'body-fluids' see Elder, 'Problems of Language in Buddhist Tantra', pp.241–2.</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> See Wayman, 'Female Energy and Symbolism', pp. 89-90; also Snellgrove, <i>The Hevajra Tantra</i> vol. I, p.27.</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> Banerjee, S. C. <i>Tantra in Bengal: A Study in Its Origin, Development and Influence</i>. Manohar. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/8185425639" class="internal">ISBN 8185425639</a>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
